                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) D(omi)ni. C(on)stat me <persName key="#Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#people/1554">Andreas</persName> gr(aci)a D(e)i <rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diac(onus)</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs> adq(ue) <rs
                            key="#Abbots">abb(as)</rs> regula <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Deacons #Abbots #Monks"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1487">S(an)c(t)i Apolenaris q(ui) voc(atur)
                            Novo</orgName> accepisse(m) et accepit a v[obis <persName><name
                                ref="Apollinaris">Apollenaris</name></persName> filio quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Rent_in_money">pensione</rs>] p(ro) <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >tres uncias int(e)g(ras)</rs> q(ui) e(st) posita in <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundu(m)</rs> q(ui) voc(atur) <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money" ref="#estates/2421"
                                ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Rent_in_money"
                                >Colopedio</placeName></geogName> cu(m) om(n)ib(us) [si]bi
                        p(er)ti[nen]tib(us), <rs key="#Fines">t(er)[ri]torio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines" ref="#estates/2422"><placeName key="#Fines"
                                ref="#places/3515">Liviense</placeName></geogName>, <rs key="#Plebs"
                            >plebe</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/1488">S(an)c(t)e
                            Re[p]arate</orgName>, q[uas per <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >enfiteusin</rs> tenere visi estis] ad iure mon(asteri)i n(ost)ri, et
                        p(er) unaquaq(ue) dic(ione) <rs key="#Rent_in_money">denarii q(ui)nq(ue)
                            tantu(m)</rs>. Unde p(ro) munimine v(est)ro feci vob(is) hoc deaccepto
                        [in mense marcio, indicione XI, <placeName ref="#places/594"
                            >Ravenne</placeName>]. Leo p(res)b(ite)r et monachus S(an)c(t)i
                        Apolinari in hoc deaccepto s(ub)s(cripsi).</ab>
